# Scope & diffs

## Minimize change surface

- Fix only what the task requires; no drive-by refactors or style churn.
- Match existing naming, types, and comment density in each folder.
- Do not modify `oz_veruach_bot/` or flagship project **logic** unless explicitly requested.

## Git

- **Never commit** unless the user asks.
- **Never push** unless the user asks.
- No `--no-verify`, force-push, or history rewrite unless explicitly instructed.
- Do not commit `.env`, `.cursor/mcp.json`, PEM keys, or live AWS resource IDs.

## Documentation

- Update README/setup when behavior or env vars change.
- Link to [`docs/AGENT-TOOLING.md`](../../docs/AGENT-TOOLING.md) when adding MCP servers or skills.

## Honesty

- If tests fail, report output — do not claim success.
- State trade-offs when a fix has downside (breaking links, requiring rebuild steps).
